For a two-player zero-sum game with payoff matrix A (row player maximizing, column player minimizing), formulate as linear programs. Row player solves: maximize v subject to A^T·p ≥ v·1, p ≥ 0, sum(p)=1. Column player solves: minimize u subject to A·q ≤ u·1, q ≥ 0, sum(q)=1. At equilibrium, v = u = game value. Computationally use scipy.optimize.linprog or cvxpy. For support enumeration, iterate over strategy subsets and solve the linear system where both players' mixed strategies satisfy A·q = u·1 and A^T·p = v·1. Verify equilibrium via mixed strategy payoff equality. Use numpy for matrix operations and iterative support checking for small games.